 Tj-310.56 -11.52  TD 0.0089  Tc -0.1289  Tw (3   For I envied the arrogant when I saw the ) Tj184.8 0  TD 0.013  Tc -0.133  Tw (prosperity of the wicked.) Tj100.8 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-285.6 -11.52  TD 0.042  Tc -0.162  Tw (4   They have no struggles; their bodies are healthy and strong.) Tj262.08 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-262.08 -11.52  TD 0.011  Tc -0.131  Tw (5   They are free from the burdens common to man; they are not plagued by human ills.) Tj362.88 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-362.88 -11.52  TD -0.019  Tc -0.101  Tw (6   Therefore pride is their necklace; they clothe themselves with violence.) Tj303.36 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-303.36 -11.52  TD 0.24  Tc 0.12  Tw (7 ) Tj7.68 0  TD -0.016  Tc -0.104  Tw (  From their callous hearts comes iniquity; the evil conceits of their minds know no limits.) Tj369.6 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-377.28 -11.52  TD 0.0265  Tc -0.1465  Tw (8   They scoff, and speak with malice; in their arrogance they threaten oppression.) Tj341.28 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-341.28 -11.52  TD 0.014  Tc -0.134  Tw (9   Their mouths lay claim to heaven, and their tongues take possession of the ) Tj323.52 0  TD 0.0994  Tc 0  Tw (earth.) Tj24.48 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-348 -11.52  TD 0.048  Tc -0.168  Tw (10  Therefore their people turn to them and drink up waters in abundance.) Tj311.04 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-311.04 -11.52  TD 0.0226  Tc -0.1426  Tw (11  They say, "How can God know? Does the Most High have knowledge?") Tj314.4 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-314.4 -11.52  TD 0.0794  Tc -0.1994  Tw (12  This is what the wicked are like) Tj146.4 0  TD 0.0034  Tc 0  Tw (--) Tj6.72 0  TD 0.0114  Tc -0.1314  Tw ( always carefree, they increase in wealth.) Tj169.44 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-322.56 -11.52  TD 0.0543  Tc -0.1743  Tw (13  Surely in vain have I) Tj102.24 0  TD 0.0312  Tc -0.1512  Tw ( kept my heart pure; in vain have I washed my hands in innocence.) Tj278.4 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-380.64 -11.52  TD 0.0508  Tc -0.1708  Tw (14  All day long I have been plagued; I have been punished every morning.) Tj312.48 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-312.48 -11.52  TD 0.0541  Tc -0.1741  Tw (15  If I had said, "I will speak thus," I would have betrayed your children.) Tj309.6 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-309.6 -11.52  TD 0.0736  Tc -0.1936  Tw (16  When I tried to understand all this) Tj159.84 0  TD -0.0341  Tc -0.0859  Tw (, it was oppressive to me) Tj98.4 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-258.24 -11.52  TD 0.026  Tc -0.146  Tw (17  till I entered the sanctuary of God; then I understood their final destiny.) Tj313.92 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-313.92 -11.52  TD 0.0231  Tc -0.1431  Tw (18  Surely you place them on slippery ground; you cast them down to ruin.) Tj308.64 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-308.64 -11.04  TD -0.0126  Tc -0.1074  Tw (19  How suddenly are they destroyed, completely swept away by terrors!) Tj294.72 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-294.72 -11.52  TD 0.1589  Tc -0.2789  Tw (20  A) Tj22.08 0  TD 0.004  Tc -0.124  Tw (s a dream when one awakes, so when you arise, O Lord, you will despise them as fantasies.) Tj374.88 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-396.96 -11.52  TD 0.0416  Tc -0.1616  Tw (21  When my heart was grieved and my spirit embittered,) Tj235.68 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-235.68 -11.52  TD 0.0359  Tc -0.1559  Tw (22  I was senseless and ignorant; I was a brute beast before you.) Tj266.4 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-266.4 -11.52  TD 0.0336  Tc -0.1536  Tw (23  Yet I am always with you; you hold me by) Tj187.2 0  TD 0.1086  Tc -0.2286  Tw ( my right hand.) Tj64.32 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-251.52 -11.52  TD 0.021  Tc -0.141  Tw (24  You guide me with your counsel, and afterward you will take me into glory.) Tj326.88 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-326.88 -11.52  TD 0.0439  Tc -0.1639  Tw (25  Whom have I in heaven but you? And earth has nothing I desire besides you.) Tj335.52 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-335.52 -11.52  TD 0.032  Tc -0.152  Tw (26  My flesh and my heart may fail, but God is the strength of my heart and my por) Tj344.16 0  TD -0.0762  Tc -0.0438  Tw (tion forever.) Tj49.92 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-394.08 -11.52  TD 0.0105  Tc -0.1305  Tw (27  Those who are far from you will perish; you destroy all who are unfaithful to you.) Tj353.28 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-353.28 -11.52  TD 0.0029  Tc -0.1229  Tw (28  But as for me, it is good to be near God. I have made the Sovereign LORD my refuge; I will tell of all ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0353  Tc -0.0847  Tw (your deeds.) Tj46.56 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-46.56 -11.52  TD /F0 10.08  Tf( ) Tj2.4 0  TD ( ) Tj-2.4 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.0737  Tc 0.708  Tw (This psalm is the first in a seri) Tj124.32 0  TD -0.0957  Tc 0.4557  Tw (es of eleven psalms that carry the name of Asaph \(Psalms 73 ) Tj247.2 0  TD 0.24  Tc 0  Tw (\226) Tj5.28 0  TD 0.0908  Tc 0.0292  Tw ( 83\). ) Tj-412.8 -11.52  TD -0.0446  Tc -0.0754  Tw (In the previous book, there was one, Psalm 50.) Tj185.28 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-185.28 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.0951  Tc 1.3251  Tw (Asaph was one of the prophets who, together with Heman and Jeduthun, had been appointed to ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0709  Tc 0.9109  Tw (conduct the music in the temple. At the bringing o) Tj206.88 0  TD -0.0866  Tc 0.6648  Tw (ver of the ark to Jerusalem, we read: \223David left Asaph ) Tj-206.88 -11.52  TD -0.0748  Tc 0.3085  Tw (and his associates before the ark of the covenant of the LORD to minister there regularly, according to each ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1188  Tc -0.0012  Tw (day\222s requirements.\224) Tj81.6 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (1) Tj3.36 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.12  Tw ( ) Tj2.4 0  TD ( ) Tj-87.36 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.0804  Tc 0.6404  Tw (Dr. Martin Lloyd Jones published a series of sermons on this psalm ) Tj277.44 0  TD -0.0426  Tc 0.2426  Tw (under the title ) Tj59.04 0  TD /F3 10.08  Tf0.1254  Tc 0.23