d more freedom to enter the sanctuary than the average Israelite. We read in Chronicles that he ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0665  Tc 0.4265  Tw (was allowed to stand before the ark: \223He) Tj164.64 0  TD -0.072  Tc 0.392  Tw ( [king David] appointed some of the Levites to minister before the ) Tj-164.64 -11.52  TD -0.0879  Tc 0.7908  Tw (ark of the LORD, to make petition, to give thanks, and to praise the LORD, the God of Israel: Asaph was ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.099  Tc 1.467  Tw (the chief, Zechariah second, then Jeiel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Mattithiah, Eliab, Bena) Tj347.52 0  TD -0.1439  Tc 1.4639  Tw (iah, Obed) Tj39.36 0  TD 0.0034  Tc 0  Tw (-) Tj3.36 0  TD -0.1024  Tc 0.7024  Tw (Edom and ) Tj-390.24 -11.52  TD -0.1392  Tc 0.6432  Tw (Jeiel. They were to play the lyres and harps, Asaph was to sound the cymbals, and Benaiah and Jahaziel the ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0574  Tc -0.0626  Tw (priests were to blow the trumpets regularly before the ark of the covenant of God.\224) Tj328.32 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (8) Tj3.36 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.12  Tw ( ) Tj2.4 0  TD ( ) Tj-298.08 -11.04  TD -0.0991  Tc 1.7619  Tw (As we mentioned earlier, the presence of the) Tj187.68 0  TD -0.1297  Tc 1.2897  Tw ( Shekinah must have been a phenomenon that was ) Tj-223.68 -11.52  TD -0.1052  Tc 0.6252  Tw (observable by the human senses. Yet, the ark stood in the tabernacle and the temple without exercising any ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0527  Tc 0.6668  Tw (influence upon the moral conduct of the Israelites. It is, evidently, possible for man to dull his con) Tj400.8 0  TD -0.1232  Tc 0.0032  Tw (science, ) Tj-400.8 -11.52  TD -0.1011  Tc 1.1179  Tw (even in the very presence of God. Thus, it was possible that Judas could embezzle money while being in ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.059  Tc 0.4948  Tw (close relationship with the Lord Jesus. Unless the Holy Spirit dwells in our heart, the presence of God will ) TjT* -0.1382  Tc 0.7382  Tw (not operate any change in us. Asaph) Tj14