l, intimate relationship with the ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0768  Tc 0.5678  Tw (Lord has no value whatsoever. That would make us like an amputate) Tj278.4 0  TD -0.0993  Tc 0.406  Tw (d member of the body of Christ. If the ) Tj-278.4 -11.52  TD -0.0379  Tc -0.0821  Tw (life of Christ does not flow through us there will be no bond with other members either. ) Tj351.36 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-315.36 -11.52  TD -0.114  Tc 1.3232  Tw (The awareness of God\222s presence immediately places Asaph\222s problems in the right perspective. ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0628  Tc 1.8628  Tw (Evidently, to begin with, Asaph b) Tj141.12 0  TD -0.1015  Tc 1.4535  Tw (egan to think about the way his own life would end. Then he made a ) Tj-141.12 -11.52  TD -0.0958  Tc 0.4558  Tw (comparison between what awaited him and what was in store for the wicked. Ultimately, every man will be ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0866  Tc 0.8626  Tw (judged according to the measure of God\222s glory. Paul says: \223All have sinned and fall ) Tj350.4 0  TD -0.0276  Tc 0.2916  Tw (short of the glory of ) Tj-350.4 -11.04  TD -0.0707  Tc 0  Tw (God.\224) Tj24 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc (10) Tj6.72 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.0894  Tc 2.1153  Tw ( If the righteous fall short, how much more the wicked! This must have been part of Asaph\222s) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-30.72 -11.52  TD -0.0728  Tc 0.4328  Tw (meditation in the presence of God. It is the glory of God which is the measuring rod of man\222s conduct, and ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0766  Tc 0.9166  Tw (it puts everything in the rig) Tj111.36 0  TD -0.065  Tc 0.521  Tw (ht perspective. If a person goes through life without God, he has nothing left at ) Tj-111.36 -11.52  TD -0.0683  Tc 2.3003  Tw (the moment of death. I do not mean that his soul will be annihilated but the only thing left will be) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0693  Tc 0.9093  Tw (hopelessness and despair when all else in life falls away. But the Book o) Tj298.56 0  TD -0.1057 