Tw ( ) Tj-273.6 -11.52  TD 0.0636  Tc 0.2964  Tw (4   We will not hide th) Tj94.56 0  TD 0.0054  Tc 0.0803  Tw (em from their children; we will tell the next generation the praiseworthy deeds of ) Tj-94.56 -11.52  TD 0.0104  Tc -0.1304  Tw (the LORD, his power, and the wonders he has done.) Tj215.52 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-215.52 -11.52  TD 0.0172  Tc -0.1625  Tw (5   He decreed statutes for Jacob and established the law in Israel, which he commanded our forefathers ) Tj0 -11.52  TD 0.0144  Tc -0.1344  Tw (to teach their chil) Tj72.96 0  TD 0.1038  Tc 0  Tw (dren,) Tj21.6 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-94.56 -11.52  TD 0.0233  Tc -0.0807  Tw (6   so the next generation would know them, even the children yet to be born, and they in turn would tell ) Tj0 -11.52  TD 0.0535  Tc -0.1735  Tw (their children.) Tj59.52 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-59.52 -11.52  TD 0.039  Tc -0.1819  Tw (7   Then they would put their trust in God and would not forget his deeds but would keep his commands.) Tj432 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-432 -11.52  TD 0.0483  Tc 0.7917  Tw (8   They would not be lik) Tj108.96 0  TD -0.0233  Tc 0.3833  Tw (e their forefathers) Tj75.36 0  TD 0.0034  Tc 0  Tw (--) Tj6.72 0  TD 0.0185  Tc 0.2882  Tw ( a stubborn and rebellious generation, whose hearts were ) Tj-191.04 -11.52  TD -0.006  Tc -0.114  Tw (not loyal to God, whose spirits were not faithful to him.) Tj227.04 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-227.04 -11.52  TD 0.0406  Tc -0.1606  Tw (9   The men of Ephraim, though armed with bows, turned back on the day of battle;) Tj347.52 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-347.52 -11.52  TD 0.0241  Tc -0.1441  Tw (10  they did not keep God's covenant a) Tj159.84 0  TD 0.0181  Tc -0.1381  Tw (nd refused to live by his law.) Tj117.6 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-277.44 -11.52  TD 0.029  Tc -0.149  Tw (11  They forgot what he had done, the wonders he had shown them.) Tj280.8 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-280.8 -11.52  TD 0.0404  Tc -0.1604  Tw (12  He did miracles in the sight of their fathers in the land of Egypt, in the region of Zoan.) Tj375.36 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-375.36 -11.52  TD 0.0451  Tc -0.1651  Tw (13  He divided the sea and led them through; he made the water st) Tj275.04 0  TD 0.0721  Tc -0.1921  Tw (and firm like a wall.) Tj84.48 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-359.52 -11.52  TD 0.0594  Tc -0.1794  Tw (14  He guided them with the cloud by day and with light from the fire all night.) Tj328.8 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-328.8 -11.52  TD 0.0483  Tc -0.1683  Tw (15  He split the rocks in the desert and gave them water as abundant as the seas;) Tj334.56 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-334.56 -11.52  TD 0.0338  Tc -0.1538  Tw (16  he brought streams out of a rocky crag and made water flow down lik) Tj303.36 0  TD -0.094  Tc -0.026  Tw (e rivers.) Tj32.16 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-335.52 -11.52  TD 0.0559  Tc -0.1759  Tw (17  But they continued to sin against him, rebelling in the desert against the Most High.) Tj365.76 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-365.76 -11.52  TD 0.0372  Tc -0.1572  Tw (18  They willfully put God to the test by demanding the food they craved.) Tj300.48 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-300.48 -11.04  TD 0.0586  Tc -0.1786  Tw (19  They spoke against God, saying, "Can God spread a table in the desert?) Tj314.88 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-314.88 -11.52  TD 0.2238  Tc 0.1362  Tw (20  Whe) Tj35.52 0  TD 0.0351  Tc -0.1018  Tw (n he struck the rock, water gushed out, and streams flowed abundantly. But can he also give us ) Tj-35.52 -11.52  TD 0.0329  Tc -0.1529  Tw (food? Can he supply meat for his people?") Tj178.08 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-178.08 -11.52  TD 0.0341  Tc -0.2684  Tw (21  When the LORD heard them, he was very angry; his fire broke out against Jacob, and his wrath rose ) Tj0 -11.52  TD 0.0535  Tc -0.1735  Tw (against Israel,) Tj60 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-60 -11.52  TD 0.24  Tc 0  Tw (2) Tj5.28 0  TD 0.007  Tc -0.127  Tw (2  for they did not believe in God or trust in his deliverance.) Tj245.76 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-251.04 -11.52  TD 0.014  Tc -0.134  Tw (23  Yet he gave a command to the skies above and opened the doors of the heavens;) Tj344.64 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-344.64 -11.52  TD 0.0373  Tc -0.1573  Tw (24  he rained down manna for the people to eat, he gave them the grain of heaven.) Tj341.76 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-341.76 -11.52  TD 0.0839  Tc -0.2039  Tw (25  Men ate the bread of ang) Tj120.48 0  TD 0.001  Tc -0.121  Tw (els; he sent them all the food they could eat.) Tj180.96 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-301.44 -11.52  TD 0.0135  Tc -0.1335  Tw (26  He let loose the east wind from the heavens and led forth the south wind by his power.) Tj370.56 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-370.56 -11.52  TD 0.0333  Tc -0.1533  Tw (27  He rained meat down on them like dust, flying birds like sand on the seashore.) Tj340.8 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-340.8 -11.52  TD 0.0026  Tc -0.1226  Tw (28  He made them come down inside t) Tj156.48 0  TD 0.0322  Tc -0.1522  Tw (heir camp, all around their tents.) Tj137.28 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-293.76 -11.52  TD 0.0403  Tc -0.1603  Tw (29  They ate till they had more than enough, for he had given them what they craved.) Tj353.28 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-353.28 -11.52  TD 0.0027  Tc -0.1227  Tw (30  But before they turned from the food they craved, even while it was still in their mouths,) Tj377.76 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-377.76 -11.52  TD 0.0479  Tc 0.6121  Tw (31  God's anger rose against them; he put) Tj180.48 0  TD 0.0364  Tc 0.3236  Tw ( to death the sturdiest among them, cutting down the young ) Tj-180.48 -11.52  TD -0.05  Tc -0.07  Tw (men of Israel.) Tj57.12 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-57.12 -11.52  TD 0.0287  Tc -0.1487  Tw (32  In spite of all this, they kept on sinning; in spite of his wonders, they did not believe.) Tj363.36 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-363.36 -11.52  TD 0.0325  Tc -0.1525  Tw (33  So he ended their days in futility and their years in terror.) Tj254.4 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-254.4 -11.52  TD 0  Tc -0.1204  Tw (34  Whenever God slew) Tj96.96 0  TD 0.0283  Tc -0.1483  Tw ( them, they would seek him; they eagerly turned to him again.) Tj255.84 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-352.8 -11.52  TD 0.0056  Tc -0.1256  Tw (35  They remembered that God was their Rock, that God Most High was their Redeemer.) Tj366.24 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-366.24 -11.52  TD 0.034  Tc -0.154  Tw (36  But then they would flatter him with their mouths, lying to him with their tongues;) Tj357.6 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-357.6 -11.52  TD 0.0185  Tc -0.1385  Tw (37  their hearts were ) Tj87.36 0  TD -0.0024  Tc -0.1176  Tw (not loyal to him, they were not faithful to his covenant.) Tj226.08 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-313.44 -11.52  TD 0.0175  Tc 1.8625  Tw (38  Yet he was merciful; he forgave their iniquities and did not destroy them. Time after time he) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj0 -11.04  TD 0.0778  Tc -0.1978  Tw (restrained his anger and did not stir up his full wrath.) Tj225.12 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-225.12 -11.52  TD 0.0127  Tc -0.1327  Tw (39  He remembered that they were but flesh,) Tj182.4 0  TD 0.0432  Tc -0.1632  Tw ( a passing breeze that does not return.) Tj157.44 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-339.84 -11.52  TD 0.0468  Tc -0.1668  Tw (40  How often they rebelled against him in the desert and grieved him in the wasteland!) Tj363.84 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-363.84 -11.52  TD 0.031  Tc -0.151  Tw (41  Again and again they put God to the test; they vexed the Holy One of Israel.) Tj329.76 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-329.76 -11.52  TD 0.0056  Tc -0.1256  Tw (42  They did not remember his power) Tj153.6 0  TD 0.0034  Tc 0  Tw (--) Tj6.72 0  TD 0.0111  Tc -0.1311  Tw ( the day h) Tj40.8 0  TD -0.0543  Tc -0.0657  Tw (e redeemed them from the oppressor,) Tj151.2 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-352.32 -11.52  TD 0.0441  Tc -0.1641  Tw (43  the day he displayed his miraculous signs in Egypt, his wonders in the region of Zoan.) Tj373.44 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-373.44 -11.52  TD -0.0012  Tc -0.1188  Tw (44  He turned their rivers to blood; they could not drink from their streams.) Tj311.04 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) TjETendstreamendobj96 0 obj10299 endobj97 0 obj<< /Type /Page /Parent 91 0 R /Resources << /Font << /F0 6 0 R /F2 12 0 R /F3 14 0 R >> /ProcSet 2 0 R >> /Contents 98 0 R >> endobj98 0 obj<< /Length 99 0 R >> stream
