f the psalmist but he uses the image to illustrate his spiritual ) Tj-120 -11.52  TD -0.0529  Tc 0.8243  Tw (condition. To him, life had been reduced to the most basic question: \223to be or not to be.\224 He is uncertain ) Tj0 -11.52  TD 0.0195  Tc -0.1395  Tw (about the outcome of it all. ) Tj110.88 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-74.88 -11.52  TD -0.1174  Tc 0.6574  Tw (I don\222t know what else can be said ab) Tj152.64 0  TD -0.0539  Tc 0.3702  Tw (out this psalm. Vs. 15 has the rather puzzling phrase: \223From ) Tj-188.64 -11.52  TD -0.1124  Tc 0.5987  Tw (my youth I have been afflicted and close to death.\224 The psalmist is evidently speaking about more than one ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1006  Tc 1.4206  Tw (catastrophic experience; his is a congenital condition. In this psalm, Heman gives a des) Tj360.96 0  TD -0.0367  Tc 0.7167  Tw (cription of man\222s ) Tj-360.96 -11.52  TD -0.0701  Tc 0.4541  Tw (sinful nature and he draw the ultimate conclusions from this. Sin has been with us since we were born, and ) Tj0 -11.04  TD -0.0625  Tc 0.5291  Tw (has kept us from entering into a meaningful relationship with our fellowmen. A lack of intimacy with God ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1046  Tc -0.0154  Tw (leads, in ) Tj35.04 0  TD -0.1059  Tc -0.0141  Tw (the ) Tj14.4 0  TD 0.0157  Tc 0.0243  Tw (last resort, to ) Tj54.72 0  TD -0.1389  Tc 0.0189  Tw (death. ) Tj25.92 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-94.08 -11.52  TD -0.1326  Tc 0.7326  Tw (It would be a sad task to analyze this psalm verse by verse. The best way seems to be, as we have ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.0652  Tc 0.6526  Tw (done, to approach it from different angles. The poem extinguishes itself as a candle that burns itself out in ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0981  Tc -0.0219  Tw (the night and leaves us in the dark, alo) Tj150.72 0  TD -0.0571  Tc -0.0629  Tw (ne with \223the God of our salvation.\224 This is the road to humility.) Tj252.48 0  TD 0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) TjETendstreamendobj259 0 obj3953 endobj260 0 o